	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>30<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Nov&#47;60</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
				<p>Rev Dr Sir&#33;Your esteemed Letter<lb/> and its <sic>inclosure</sic> I duly recd. &#38; the latter<lb/> I herewith return.  I had to see <persName>Mr Goldsmith</persName><lb/> <persName>Dr Bondy</persName> &#38; others which delayed my reply.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Our address left here several weeks<lb/> ago.  The one <add>&#63;</add> by <persName>Dr Bondi</persName> <add>&#63;</add><lb/> much revision &#38; improvement&#44; was numerously<lb/> signed &#38; by this time is&#8212;no doubt&#8212;in<lb/> the hands of the venerable Rabbi.  The<lb/> general opinion is that under the<lb/> circumstances we cannot with<lb/> propriety sign a second address.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">As to publishing a second<lb/> Edition of Devotl. Exercises&#44; I am as yet<lb/> undecided.  But should I make up my<lb/> mind&#44; I will assuredly address myself<lb/> to you on the subject.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My thanksgiving discourse yesterday<lb/> has caused some sensation &#38; is published<lb/> this morning in several of the dailies</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>I send you for insertion in the<lb/> Occident if you think proper&#8212;a copy<lb/> of the world which has it more<lb/> correctly than the Herald &#38;c.  should<lb/> you insert it please not to divide<lb/> it.  In the text it should be &#8220;The<lb/> nations thank Thee O God&#8221; instead<lb/> of &#8220;O Lord&#8221; as the papers have it</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Very respectfully yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">M J Raphall Dr</persName></p>
		</body>
	</text>
